# Switch

IDS Switches are used as a binary choice input that gives users the ability to trigger a state with real time feedback.
IDS Switches offer a binary choice input that gives users the ability to trigger a state with real time feedback.

## Installation & Import

```bash
yarn add @ids-ts/switch
```

```tsx
import { Switch } from '@ids-ts/switch';
```

## Props

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `checked` | `boolean` | No | Controlled checked state. |
| `onChange` | `(e: ChangeEvent<HTMLInputElement>) => void` | No | Called when the toggle state changes. |
| `children` | `ReactNode` | No | Label text displayed next to the switch. |
| `disabled` | `boolean` | No | Disables the switch when true. |
| `automationId` | `string` | No | Test automation identifier. |
| `aria-label` | `string` | No | Accessible label when no visible label is used. |

